<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="38" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="39.[192,1327,1602,1626]" box="[192,1327,1602,1626]" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,302,1602,1626]" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Ecology</emphasis>
. Lowland. Epigean. Bare stream banks. Gregarious. Diurnal; active on mat plants.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[192,1440,1665,1690]" box="[192,1440,1665,1690]" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,295,1665,1689]" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Biology</emphasis>
. Seasonality: February. Tenerals: February. One specimen infested with fungi (Laboulbeniales).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[192,1440,1729,1786]" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,416,1729,1754]" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Dispersal power</emphasis>
. Macropterous, probably capable of flight. Moderate runner. Vagility likely favoured by flight capacity.
</paragraph>
